bibdata.title: Refactor the LocationMapsGeneratorService so that we don't take an extra label in the locations template
Figure out why we are getting triple location labels

comments.body:
We get a triple library label because we follow the concept from voyager. With Alma we can get the library and the location of the library without needing to add the library label in front of them. We need to refactor the generate method in the `LocationMapsGeneratorService` so that we create the locations template but without appending the library label in front of the holding label. 
I will open a new issue to work on that. https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/issues/1133

orangelight.title: Remove `?` from methods that don't return boolean

comments.body:
## account_controller#index

First fetches patron "first_name", "last_name", "barcode" from bibdata using the netit.

Then it hits voyager to get the account object with the following properties:
- avail_items has keys:
  - itemID
  - itemTitle
  - expireDate
  - pickuplocation
- request_items has keys:
  - itemID
  - itemTitle
  - expireDate
  - pickuplocation
  - queuePosition
- fines_fees has keys:
  - date
  - title
  - postingType
  - amount
  - balance
- charged_items has keys:
  - itemId
  - renewable
  - title
  - dueDate
- borrowing_blocks has keys:
  - patronGroupName
  - blockCount
  - blockReason

https://github.com/tulibraries/alma_rb/blob/main/lib/alma/user.rb#L9 this `expand` option is making me think there's an undocumented option on https://developers.exlibrisgroup.com/alma/apis/docs/users/R0VUIC9hbG1hd3MvdjEvdXNlcnM=/ to get everything we need in 1 call. If so we'd pull it through the bibdata endpoint.

update: that expand only gives the total numbers / amounts. But if we pull that we can use it to determine whether we need to hit the other endpoints.

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/37861882/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/37861882)

Coverage decreased (-0.005%) to 96.584% when pulling **4b1bf8ae9bbe94bc5e6025ef861ddea679be1705 on 2368-delete-demerits** into **8584aea22904d9be3ddfcf0644bf82bfc293837f on main**.
